ZCZC OE41
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 072300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING A DEEP LOW IS EXP TO BE NEAR SE ICELAND AROUND 968
MOV E. AT THE SAME TIME AN EWARD TRAVELLING RIDGE LIES TO W OF 30 W 1025.
THROUGH MONDAY AND TUESDAY THE NERN LOW MOVS E INTO NERN SCANDINAVIA FLN.
AT THE SAME TIME THE RIDGE MOVS E TO LIE ACROSS SERN BRITAIN BY MIDDAY TUESDAY.
ON WEDNESDAY A NEW DPN LOW IS LIKELY TO MOV NE TOWARDS OR CLOSE TO ICELAND
WITH AN ASSOCIATED FRONTAL TROUGH CROSSING THE BRITISH ISLES AS THE RIDGE
DECLINES E. HOWEVER A NEW WEAK RIDGE FOLLOWS ACROSS IRELAND LATER. A RISK
OF WIDESPREAD GALE FORCE WINDS ACROSS N PORTPATRICK MAINLY N OF 58 N ON
SUNDAY EVENING WITH SEV GALES IN PLACES. THESE WINDS TRANSFER E THROUGH
MONDAY BEFORE GRADUALLY ABATING FM THE W. A RENEWED RISK OF A SWATHE OF
NEAR GALE LOC GALE FORCE WINDS MOV NE LATER TUESDAY AND THROUGH WEDNESDAY
FOR NW AND N PORTPATRICK
NNNN